[{"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Threads finally lets you delete your account separately from Instagram", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Threads logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XQXyXEHjUwSJRM1hOCUgitUhrHg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72862057/STK156_Instagram_threads_3.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"HQVdsw\">Meta is rolling out a way for you to delete your Threads profile without having to delete your Instagram account, too. You\u2019ll be able to access the new feature from the settings menu in a new \u201cDelete or Deactivate Profile\u201d section, according to <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@mosseri/post/Czmfy17SDfl\">a post from Instagram boss Adam Mosseri</a>. I don\u2019t have the feature yet myself, but I suspect Meta will make it available to everyone soon enough.</p>\n<p id=\"h8M1Oa\">This new ability to delete <em>just</em> your Threads profile addresses an early complaint with the app, which currently requires that you <a href=\"https://help.instagram.com/1747515265645443\">sign up with", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23959709/threads-delete-account-instagram-keep-meta", "date_published": "2023-11-13T22:07:04+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Rick and Morty\u2019s Dan Harmon and Scott Marder are trusting the process for season 7", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A boy in a yellow shirt sitting in the passenger seat of a small spaceship alongside an old man in a blue T-shirt and a lab coat.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yo7sDQUN1KgWRfXTtRGo4Lk-nOY=/0x0:1620x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72861668/RAM_704c.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Adult Swim</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Rick and Morty co-creator Dan Harmon and executive producer Scott Marder say that being in a healthier space personally is a big part of what\u2019s making the new season so sharp.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23951296/rick-and-morty-dan-harmon-scott-marder-interview-season-7\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23951296/rick-and-morty-dan-harmon-scott-marder-interview-season-7", "date_published": "2023-11-13T20:30:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Einride\u2019s drone truck has its first full-time job moving GE appliances around", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Boxy black-and-white truck with no windshield up front\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3Lt_Ns71Kj3zRayGyp5_nmMTDqE=/0x0:3999x2666/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72861546/Einride_Selmer_9.jpg_2.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>There is no calling shotgun in this truck because there are no seats for humans.</em> | Image: Einride</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"0X6eeG\">The Swedish autonomous trucking company Einride is using its cab-less electric delivery vehicles in Selmer, Tennessee, to move items from GE Appliances\u2019 manufacturing plant to a warehouse. This operation can run up to seven shuttles per day, Monday through Thursday, <a href=\"https://www.einride.tech/press/first-fulltime-autonomous-operations\">the press release states</a>. In an email to <em>The Verge</em>, a PR representative for Einride, Matthew Klein, wrote that the distance for each trip is 0.3 miles (or 0.48km) and is all on private roads owned by GE.</p>\n<p i", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23959030/einride-driverless-trucks-ge-appliances-autonomous-delivery", "date_published": "2023-11-13T19:55:18+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "A Google witness let slip just how much it pays Apple for Safari search", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Google\u2019s wordmark, written in red and pink on a dark blue background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/f9XrFQyUlVYnaGh0EpHI5HHMGMc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72861540/STK093_Google_06.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"QqWhz5\">Google gives Apple a 36 percent cut of all search ad revenue that comes from Safari, according to University of Chicago professor Kevin Murphy. Google had fought to keep the number confidential, but <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-11-13/apple-gets-36-of-google-revenue-from-search-deal-witness-says?sref=ExbtjcSG\"><em>Bloomberg</em> reports</a> that Murphy shared the figure while testifying in Google\u2019s defense today at the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23869483/us-v-google-search-antitrust-case-updates\">Google antitrust trial</a>. </p>\n<p id=\"MzsZti\">Google has long paid to be the default search en", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23959353/google-apple-safari-search-revenue-antitrust-trial", "date_published": "2023-11-13T19:52:53+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Netflix says the cloud will let it expand beyond mobile games", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot from the video game Hades.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xaVjB9Snqu6ce8Mr5wYjlxgUq4s=/300x0:1920x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72861416/ss_bcb499a0dd001f4101823f99ec5094d2872ba6ee.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A mobile version of </em>Hades<em> is coming to Netflix in 2024.</em> | Image: Supergiant Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"7AtEeB\">As Netflix\u2019s foray into cloud gaming expands, so, too, will the kinds of games the company offers. \u201cWe feel like there is a real big opportunity with cloud to create a certain type of game experience that really is tailored to Netflix on TV,\u201d says Leanne Loombe, Netflix\u2019s head of external games.</p>\n<p id=\"G7m8M8\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/16/23919517/netflix-game-streaming-beta-tvs-us\">Netflix\u2019s cloud gaming efforts are still very early</a> and follow nearly two years of releasing games exclusively on mobile. Right now, only two titles are availab", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23958926/netflix-cloud-gaming-tv-games-leanne-loombe-interview", "date_published": "2023-11-13T19:27:39+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Amazon is getting rid of its gaming content channel amid larger games layoffs", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Amazon\u2019s logo on a black, orange, and tan background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9e7f3s3Gj43VO4xOBuZZmFAdrGY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72861330/acastro_STK103__01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"vJ55Ps\">Amazon is cutting \u201cjust over\u201d 180 jobs in its games division and making some changes to its games initiatives, according to a memo sent to employees by VP of Amazon Games Christoph Hartmann. The changes include shutting down its <a href=\"https://www.twitch.tv/crown\">Crown channel</a> that streams on Twitch, closing its <a href=\"https://www.amazon.jobs/en/landing_pages/game%20growth\">Game Growth</a> effort that helps game makers market their products, and \u201crefocusing\u201d the work it does with its free games offered through Prime Gaming. </p>\n<p id=\"AVCVCP\">\u201cWe are proud of the work the teams have been doing, pushing into ne", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23959224/amazon-gaming-layoffs-crown-content-channel", "date_published": "2023-11-13T19:06:32+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Amazon\u2019s latest Fire TV Stick 4K Max is on sale for a new low price", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An Amazon Fire TV Stick 4K Max streaming stick with its remote sitting beside a bowl of popcorn in front of a TV.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/c2w5AOwTK1HuYc10ScUaxIDnosc=/0x29:1210x836/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72861181/Fire_TV_Stick_4K_Max_Image_1.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The new Fire TV Stick 4K Max looks just like any old streaming stick from Amazon, but its upgrades are most prominent on the inside.</em> | Image: Amazon</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bQkCDb\">As Black Friday deals continue trickling in early, more recent devices are going on sale for the first time or for new lows. One example is <strong>Amazon\u2019s new Fire TV Stick 4K Max</strong>, which came out just a couple of months ago and is now on sale for $39.99 ($20 off) at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BP9SNVH9?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a> and <a href=\"https://howl.me/ckZO8Hjol79\">Best Buy<", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23958927/amazon-firetv-stick-4k-max-sharge-shargeek-seethrough-power-bank-deal-sale", "date_published": "2023-11-13T18:36:39+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "ExxonMobil is a lithium company now", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of an ExxonMobil gas station\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ZLM6RnTguiEzboYFQ1Fd7LYzXqw=/0x0:4000x2667/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72861042/1557172918.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Getty</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Ez0kG1\">ExxonMobil is getting into the lithium production business. The <a href=\"https://investor.exxonmobil.com/news-events/press-releases/detail/1152/exxonmobil-drilling-first-lithium-well-in-arkansas-aims-to\">company announced on Monday</a> that it\u2019s going to become a \u201cleading producer of lithium\u201d by opening its first drilling operation in southern Arkansas.</p>\n<p id=\"58mw02\">The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/8/31/23330537/ev-battery-mineral-shortage-us-tax-credits\">demand for lithium</a> has grown in the past couple of years, with the metal serving as a key ingredient in the rechargeable batteries that power electric vehicles, phones, laptops, and other tech. ExxonMobil plans to s", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23958935/exxonmobil-lithium-drilling-arkansas", "date_published": "2023-11-13T18:04:45+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "We only get one planet", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A digital collage of a variety of softly rendered illustrations showing pixelated chaffs of wheat, a car tire, growing grass, and a circuit board maze.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5q8MzReExyWuTQxSINZxS9HfbDY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72839251/236801_Sustainability_Package_ARTBOARDS_CVirginia_LEDE_2040x1360.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustrations by Nico H. Brausch for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"OgARfS\">Sustainability is one of those words that has lost most of its meaning thanks to a steady drumbeat of corporate marketing and greenwashing. \u201cGoing green\u201d often means buying some useless carbon credits or slapping a few choice buzzwords on a label. Rarely does it seem to hold any value anymore. </p>\n<p id=\"YiNCPe\">But as the planet careens toward a future made uncertain by climate change, true environmental stewardship requires we take a closer look at the meaning of sustainability \u2014 and ", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23943463/sustainability-tech-climate-change-ai-housing-ev", "date_published": "2023-11-13T17:39:10+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Remedy Entertainment\u2019s newest game pivots away from free-to-play", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Control featuring the main character silhouetted by a red background pushing away an enemy.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/PSwe7w9MztrwYfwP6RO-EP2qX_0=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72860751/Control_Screenshot_12.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Remedy Entertainment</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"SQHT4L\">Remedy Entertainment, the studio behind <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23934662/alan-wake-2-review-ps5-xbox-pc\">that one game that\u2019s having a moment right now</a>, has announced that its upcoming game, codenamed Vanguard, <a href=\"https://investors.remedygames.com/announcements/remedy-entertainment-plc-remedy-entertainment-plans-to-reboot-codename-vanguard-to-a-premium-game-with-a-strong-cooperative-multiplayer-component/\">is pivoting from a free-to-play model to a premium one</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"vIlFx7\"><em>Vanguard</em> <a href=\"https://investors.remedygames.com/announcements/remedy-enter", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23958953/remedy-entertainment-premium-game-free-to-play", "date_published": "2023-11-13T17:01:15+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The Garfield Movie\u2019s new trailer will put you in a real Monday kind of mood", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/X7JuheCloFfrbXxNIP9kNXhIDj4=/286x0:2595x1539/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72860687/Screen_Shot_2023_11_13_at_9.17.36_AM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Columbia</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"hkgWV6\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/3/17/23645093/super-mario-bros-movie-chris-pratt-mario-voice-nintendo\">Chris Pratt\u2019s turn as Mario</a> worked because Illumination and Nintendo took care to make sure <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23669598/super-mario-bros-movie-review\"><em>The Super Mario Bros. Movie\u2019</em></a>s red-hatted plumber sounded distinct yet enough like Charles Martinet\u2019s take on the character to pass the smell test. For fans of Jim Davis\u2019 <em>Garfield </em>comics, there was hope that Columbia might take a similar approach with <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/11/1/22758214/chris-pratt-garfield-movie-mario\"><em>The Garfield Movie</em></a>, its new animated feature from dire", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23958789/garfield-the-movie-trailer-chris-pratt", "date_published": "2023-11-13T16:57:39+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "WhatsApp is adding a new way to voice chat with large groups", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshots of the new voice chat feature.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4LXOBv00covUiB8a7OJ9_GmAdUw=/0x0:1414x943/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72860602/WhatsApp_Image_2023_11_13_at_15.09.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Voice chats don\u2019t automatically ring everyone in a group.</em> | Image: WhatsApp</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"r2L76U\">WhatsApp is rolling out a new voice chat feature in the coming weeks that\u2019s designed to be a less disruptive way to conduct voice calls in large groups. The feature was <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/8/7/23822689/whatsapp-voice-chat-android-beta-rollout\">previously spotted releasing in beta</a>, but WhatsApp <a href=\"https://faq.whatsapp.com/868728454494559/?helpref=hc_fnav\">has now made the news official</a>. </p>\n<p id=\"5s7lzZ\">Although it\u2019s long been possible to <a href=\"https://faq.whatsapp.com/829612741557179/?helpref=hc_fnav&amp;cms_platform=android\">voice call on WhatsApp ", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23958889/whatsapp-voice-chat-feature-ios-android-32-users", "date_published": "2023-11-13T16:35:58+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Zelle banks have been paying back scam victims after government pressure", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of two smartphones sitting on a yellow background with red tape across them that reads \u201cDANGER\u201d\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/bgGv3jWwaqZksI1rJrTnH9JGJwQ=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72860557/akrales_220309_4977_0336.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Z0X5wn\">The banks that participate in the Zelle payments app owned by JPMorgan Chase, Bank of America, and others have relented in their refusal to pay back victims of imposter scams. <a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/technology/cybersecurity/payments-app-zelle-begins-refunds-imposter-scams-after-washington-pressure-2023-11-13/\"><em>Reuters</em> reported</a> today that the repayments started on June 30th and were a response to lawmaker pressure on the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) to compel lenders to reimburse victims.</p>\n<p id=\"HRKQVQ\">Banks leaned on the f", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23958769/zelle-banks-refunding-imposter-scam-victims", "date_published": "2023-11-13T16:28:47+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Nvidia is launching a new must-have AI chip \u2014\u00a0as customers still scramble for its last one", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NmX6uP63pJpq2PPEID6yVZ4Mn1c=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72860466/nvidia_hgx_h200.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Nvidia\u2019s HGX H200.</em> | Image: Nvidia</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"LmgQbI\">Nvidia is introducing a new top-of-the-line chip for AI work, the HGX H200. The new GPU upgrades the wildly in demand <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/3/22/22989182/nvidia-ai-hopper-architecture-h100-gpu-eos-supercomputer\">H100</a> with 1.4x more memory bandwidth and 1.8x more memory capacity, improving its ability to handle intensive generative AI work.</p>\n<p id=\"dwygS0\">The big question is whether companies will be able to get their hands on the new chips or whether they\u2019ll be as supply constrained as the H100 \u2014 and Nvidia doesn\u2019t quite have an answer for that. The first H200 chips will be released in the second quarter of 2024, and <a href=\"https://nvidianews.nvidia.com/news", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23958823/nvidia-h200-ai-gpu-announced-specs-release-date", "date_published": "2023-11-13T16:04:38+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The Verge\u2019s favorite holiday gifts under $50", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of hands holding various products on a brightly colored background of stars.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/y3D6gomoRJ6DQHcOjUXr3cmWoC0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72860202/236830_UNDER_50_Gift_Guide_Artboards_CVirginia_LEDE_2040x1360.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo Illustration by Amelia Holowaty Krales and Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Gift-giving doesn\u2019t have to eat up all of your time and money \u2014 and we\u2019ve rounded up an assortment of inexpensive gifts to prove it.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23952179/tech-gifts-under-50-best-cheap-ideas-2023-budget\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23952179/tech-gifts-under-50-best-cheap-ideas-2023-budget", "date_published": "2023-11-13T15:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Sony\u2019s Pulse Explore earbuds deliver immersive audio and one very useful trick", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of Sony\u2019s Pulse Explore wireless earbuds.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/84sJpAsKGR4o0rWX2dY-7oc_Ho4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72860110/DSCF4001_Enhanced_NR.0.jpg\" />\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The first wireless earbuds from Sony\u2019s PlayStation unit have unique planar magnetic drivers and an equally unique style.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23957860/sony-pulse-explore-playstation-earbuds-impressions\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23957860/sony-pulse-explore-playstation-earbuds-impressions", "date_published": "2023-11-13T14:35:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The fight to save old video games", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A stylized version of the Vergecast logo, showing old video games.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/IcS9vkidAUbGULow2_j7ReB6wwg=/0x3:3244x2166/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72860033/Retro_Games_3000x2000px.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Samar Haddad / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"CllNkA\">When I ask Frank Cifaldi, the founder and director of the Video Game History Foundation, to explain the importance of preserving and maintaining old video games, he answers with a movie analogy. Imagine, he said, \u201cif movies were only released on, like, VHS, ever. You want to watch <em>Back to the Future? </em>All right, you have to go on eBay, and you have to find an antique VHS copy that\u2019s degraded a bit from use. You have to find a VCR that works, a TV that it plugs into \u2014 or the external scalers that make it look correct on your modern TV \u2014 and you might need a time-base corrector because the magnetic flux signal ", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23958715/video-game-emulation-preservation-vergecast", "date_published": "2023-11-13T14:06:31+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Sony\u2019s PlayStation Portal gives a confusing first impression", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The PlayStation Portal resting on a glass coffee table.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9asKWQWIvDvnhiqmzmyn1ZO2u7w=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72859994/111323_PlayStation_Portal_ADiBenedetto_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Portal boots up and prompts you to connect to your PlayStation 5. Beyond that, there\u2019s not much going on.</em></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p class=\"p--has-dropcap p-large-text\" id=\"6UB64u\">Sony\u2019s new PlayStation Portal that launches November 15th is a $199.99 device that does just one thing: it streams games via Wi-Fi off of your home PlayStation 5, requiring that you already own Sony\u2019s pricey console.</p>\n<p id=\"0iXMkB\">It doesn\u2019t do any kind of cloud streaming like Nvidia\u2019s Geforce Now or Sony\u2019s own PlayStation Plus Premium subscription, and it can\u2019t run anything locally (not even YouTube or Netflix). The Portal is purpose-built to use a singular feature Sony first debuted with t", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23958572/sony-playstation-portal-ps5-streaming-remote-play-handheld-specs-impressions", "date_published": "2023-11-13T14:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The right-to-repair movement is just getting started", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Conceptual illustration of a pair of hands repairing a smart phone. The screen of the phone has been removed to reveal a circuit board maze with a tree in the center, intended to communicate the political hurdles of the right-to-repair movement.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/f3vipr3muEPzZjGHzo_L_kJH8L8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72859909/236801_Right_To_Repair_Nico_Brausch.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nico H. Brausch for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Apple stunned the world when it came out in support of California\u2019s right-to-repair law. But software locks and other obstacles seem to signal that the fight is far from over.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23951200/right-to-repair-law-apple-ifixit-iphone\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23951200/right-to-repair-law-apple-ifixit-iphone", "date_published": "2023-11-13T13:30:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Secretary of Energy Jennifer Granholm on cleaning up \u2018clean\u2019 energy", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage of Secretary of Energy Jennifer Granholm.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4OCIhUGtTDBa8fq3OvfXdivntuI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72859806/236801_Sustainability_SECRETARY_ARTBOARDS_CVirginia_2_LEDE_2040x1360.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo Illustration by Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos by Dee Dwyer for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The US is the world\u2019s biggest producer of oil and gas. Can Granholm chart a path to a more sustainable future?</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23951210/energy-secretary-jennifer-granholm-interview-sustainability\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23951210/energy-secretary-jennifer-granholm-interview-sustainability", "date_published": "2023-11-13T13:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Google fights scammers using Bard hype to spread malware", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of Google\u2019s multicolor \u201cG\u201d logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qg6uG060a9TX40rjAXLf8DGSTdE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72859587/STK093_Google_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"OTeGTQ\">Google is suing scammers who are trying to use the hype around generative AI to trick people into downloading malware, the company has announced. In a lawsuit filed today in California, the company says individuals believed to be based in Vietnam are setting up social media pages and running ads encouraging users to \u201cdownload\u201d its generative AI service Bard. The download actually delivers malware to the victims, which steals social media credentials for the scammers to use.</p>\n<p id=\"21jd23\">\u201cDefendants are three individuals whose identities are unknown who claim to provide, among other things, \u201cthe latest version\u201d of Google Bard for download,\u201d the lawsuit r", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/13/23958629/google-scammers-bard-ai-malware-spread-lawsuit", "date_published": "2023-11-13T11:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}]